==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*kwiðan'': cognate with Old Frisian [[qwetha]], Old Saxon [[queþan]], Old High German [[quedan]], Old Norse [[kveða]], Gothic [[𐌵𐌹𐌸𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'kweðan/

===Verb===
'''cweþan''' (class V strong: '''cwiþþ''' ‘he says’, '''cwæþ''' ‘he said’, {{Unicode|'''cwǣdon'''}} ‘they said’, ('''ġe''')'''cweden''' past participle)
# to [[say]], [[tell]]

===Descendents===
*Modern English [[quethe]]

